The paper deals with the vulnerability of deep learning algorithms to adversarial examples in the domain of malware detection, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also uses explainable machine learning algorithms to interpret the decisions of deep neural networks, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the characteristics of malware binaries and proposes a novel attack algorithm, which could be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and computer vision (cs.CV) subfields.
